sols_latex:
Multiplying the numerator and denominator by $\sqrt{1+2x} + 1$ yields:

\begin{align*}
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{x}{\sqrt{1+2x} - 1} &= \lim_{x \to 0} \left(\frac{x}{\sqrt{1+2x} - 1} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{1+2x} + 1}{\sqrt{1+2x} + 1}\right)
\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{x(\sqrt{1+2x} + 1)}{(\sqrt{1+2x})^2 - 1^2}
\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{x(\sqrt{1+2x} + 1)}{(1+2x) - 1}
\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sqrt{1+2x} + 1}{2}
\\ &= \frac{\sqrt{1+2\cdot0} + 1}{2}
\\ &= {\color{blue} 1}
\end{align*}

